members.name: BroadcastPath

members.docComment:
/**
 * Extracts the file extension from a BroadcastPath.
 *
 * @param path - The BroadcastPath to extract extension from
 *
 * @returns The file extension including the dot (e.g., ".json", ".txt") or empty string if no extension
 *
 * @example
 *
 * getExtension("/alice.json") // returns ".json" getExtension("/video/stream") // returns "" getExtension("/file.min.js") // returns ".js"
 */
members.name: extension

members.docComment:
/**
 * Runtime type guard to check if a string is a valid BroadcastPath.
 *
 * @param path - The string to validate
 *
 * @returns true if the path is a valid BroadcastPath
 */
members.name: isValidBroadcastPath

members.docComment:
/**
 * Runtime type guard to check if a string is a valid TrackPrefix.
 *
 * @param path - The string to validate
 *
 * @returns true if the path is a valid TrackPrefix
 */
members.name: isValidPrefix
TrackPrefix

members.docComment:
/**
 * Validates and returns a BroadcastPath, throwing an error if invalid.
 *
 * @param path - The string to validate
 *
 * @returns The validated BroadcastPath
 *
 * @throws
 *
 * Error if the path is not a valid BroadcastPath
 */
members.name: validateBroadcastPath

members.docComment:
/**
 * Validates and returns a TrackPrefix, throwing an error if invalid.
 *
 * @param path - The string to validate
 *
 * @returns The validated TrackPrefix
 *
 * @throws
 *
 * Error if the path is not a valid TrackPrefix
 */
members.name: validateTrackPrefix
